{"id":"math140-vareval2-cr001","cid":"MATH 140","topic":"Functions Cost Revenue Profit","subtopic":"Evaluating cost and revenue functions","difficulty":1,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"A company's revenue function is R(x) = {a}x^2 + {b}, where x is hundreds of units. Find R({x_val}).","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":-5,"max":-1},"b":{"type":"int","min":100,"max":400},"x_val":{"type":"int","min":2,"max":6}},"answer_expr":"vareval2","steps":["R({x_val}) = {a}({x_val})^2 + {b} = {ax2} + {b} = {answer_vareval2}."],"tags":["business-calculus","functions","revenue","quadratic"]}
